                     <interp inst="t18201028-68-person766" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had a niece named 
               <persName id="t18201028-68-person767">
                  Harriet 
                  Cole
               <interp inst="t18201028-68-person767" type="surname" value="Cole"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-68-person767" type="given" value="Harriet"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-68-person767" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , she married the prisoner - she led a very indifferent life. I saw her after her marriage, she told me he was gone to sea and applied to me several times for money. It is nine years since I heard any thing of her. I live in New-street, Dorset-square. I think she is dead.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-68-person768">
